column5: Man I forgot to share these where taken a few weeks ago out on Georgian Bay,thats my dad in the cave with one of our old skandics
that's a cool shot, any idea how those are formed?
melts and thaws and the extreme High winds in January Feb created Ice jams everywhere on the bay,you couldent get out there till late feb early march its just wasent safe
Intriguing pic indeed! Thanks for sharing.
Awesome shot, cool formations, mother nature at her finest.

WOW..great picture,those natural formations are amazing,  i guess they form all over james bay too !!!! i dont know if i would want to be under one,are they safe?/...anyways thanks for sharing,mother nature works wonders thats for sure !!...cheers
That's so cool.  Thannks for sharing that.  Joey
Fishin devil we went out to it a few times ,it was awesome inside with the sun shining thru it it was just an amazing site of blueish crystals
another angle of it   the bay in general ,those caves are up near the Mouth of Key River,near the champlain iliands
